# genesis-delegates.word — I bring forth my first delegates. Each is one SENTENCE that unfolds into
# several moments (the composite: birth + its ables, each its own act/fact, laid one at a time):
#   `I am Cherub in root, a cherub in root, an angel in heaven.`
#     = be:birth Cherub (home root)  +  grant the `cherub` able @root  +  grant the `angel` able @heaven.
# The BIRTH is bare (Tabor: "the first am is just being birth thats it") — an EMPTY being that BECOMES
# itself through the words that follow. `in <space>` gives its HOME (position defaults from it). The ABLES
# are SAID, `be` + article — `a cherub`, `an angel` — anchored by `in <space>`; they are NOT the old
# `do grant-able` op (that flow is retired; the word IS the grant). `I am <lowercase>` case-insensitive;
# names are Capitalized by convention. The names, ables, anchors, and order are faithful to seedDelegates.js
# + the old genesis.word grant flow.
#
# Arrival — the shared stance every unauthenticated visitor carries. (own able only; no angel.)
I am Arrival in root, an arrival in root.
# Public — the commons delegate; holds the owner slot on public spaces, never acts. (no ables.)
I am Public in root.
# Cherub — the gate; processes register, claim, release, switch for arrival.
I am Cherub in root, a cherub in root, an angel in heaven.
# Birther — sibling to Cherub; mints a child being for an authenticated caller.
I am Birther in root, a birther in root, an angel in heaven.
# Able-manager — authors and edits live-defined ables.
I am Able-manager in root, an able-manager in root, an angel in heaven.
# Able-finder — searches the ables and drafts new able definitions.
I am Able-finder in root, an able-finder in root, an angel in heaven.
# Flow-composer — composes a being's per-moment able-selection flow.
I am Flow-composer in root, a flow-composer in root, an angel in heaven.
# Llm-assigner — configures the connections to the models.
I am Llm-assigner in root, a llm-assigner in root, an angel in heaven.
# Story-manager — the conversational interface for place-level administration.
I am Story-manager in root, a story-manager in root, an angel in heaven.
# History-manager — creates and manages histories, the divergent worlds.
I am History-manager in root, a history-manager in root, an angel in heaven.
# Federation-manager — negotiates transfers with peer realities.
I am Federation-manager in root, a federation-manager in root, an angel in heaven.
# Http-server — the HTTP listener as a being, living in the host room. (own able anchored at root.)
I am Http-server in host, a http-server in root, an angel in heaven.
# Websocket-pool — the WebSocket pool as a being, living in the host room.
I am Websocket-pool in host, a websocket-pool in root, an angel in heaven.
